ğŸ–¥ï¸ Part 1: EC2 Instance Setup (Ubuntu 20.04)
Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance
- OS: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS
- Instance Type: t2.micro
- Security Groups: SSH 22 (My IP), HTTP 80 (Anywhere), HTTPS 443 (Optional)
- Description: Ye VM server banayenge jahan hum manually apps deploy kar sakte hain.

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Part 2: SSH Access & Basic Tools Install
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@<ec2-public-ip>
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y git python3-pip awscli
- Description: EC2 ko connect karna aur git, pip, awscli install karna for further work.

ğŸ§° Part 3: AWS CLI Configuration
aws configure
- Description: AWS CLI configure karna IAM user ki keys ke sath taake command line se AWS services access ho saken.

ğŸ Part 4: Create Flask App Locally
mkdir flaskapp && cd flaskapp
nano application.py
- Paste Flask app code:
  from flask import Flask
  application = Flask(__name__)
  @application.route('/')
  def home():
      return "Hello from AWS Elastic Beanstalk!"
  if __name__ == "__main__":
      import os
      port = int(os.environ.get('PORT', 8080))
      application.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=port)
- Description: Simple Flask web app banayi jisse EB pe deploy karenge.

ğŸ“¦ Part 5: Create Required Files
echo "flask" > requirements.txt
echo "gunicorn" >> requirements.txt
echo "python-3.9" > runtime.txt
- Description: Flask aur Gunicorn dependencies aur Python runtime specify karna EB ke liye.

ğŸ“¦ Part 6: Elastic Beanstalk CLI Install
sudo apt install python3-pip -y
pip3 install --upgrade --user awsebcli
echo 'export PATH=~/.local/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
eb --version
- Description: EB CLI install karna taake app deploy aur manage kar saken.

ğŸš€ Part 7: Initialize Elastic Beanstalk
eb init -p python-3.9 flaskapp --region us-east-1
- Description: EB app initialize karna aur SSH key attach karna.

ğŸŒ Part 8: Create Environment & Deploy
eb create flask-env
- Description: Environment create karke Flask app deploy karna.

ğŸ” Part 10: Check Live URL
eb open
- Description: Browser mein app live URL check karna.

ğŸ”§ Part 11: Check Logs (If Health = RED)
eb logs
- Description: Agar app health red ho to logs check kar ke fix karna.

ğŸ§¹ Part 12: Clean Up (If Needed)
eb terminate flask-env --force
eb create flask-env
- Description: Broken environment ko terminate aur re-create karna.

ğŸ›  Link Flask App to GitHub
cd /home/ubuntu/flaskapp
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/shan376/flaskapp.git
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Flask app for Elastic Beanstalk deployment"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main --force
- Description: Project GitHub pe push karna taake version control aur sharing possible ho.

ğŸ§¹ Optional Cleanup: Add .gitignore
nano .gitignore
- Paste content:
  __pycache__/
  *.pyc
  *.log
  .env
  .venv/
git add .gitignore
git commit -m "Add .gitignore to exclude temp files"
git push
- Description: Cache aur sensitive files Git se exclude karna.

ğŸ“Œ Assignment â€“ AWS Lambda: Create & Test First Function
1. Go to Lambda Console
2. Click Create function â†’ Author from scratch
3. Fill Info: Function name: HelloLambda, Runtime: Python 3.9, Architecture: x86_64, Execution Role: basic Lambda permissions
4. Click Create
5. Add code:
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    return {
        'statusCode': 200,
        'body': 'Hello from AWS Lambda!'
    }
6. Click Deploy
7. Test function: Configure test event, click Test
8. Check output: {"statusCode": 200, "body": "Hello from AWS Lambda!"}
9. (Optional) Set up Function URL for public access
- Description: Simple serverless function banayi aur test kiya, optional URL se browser ya app se call kar sakte hain.
